Namaste friends,
 
A mail on vedic-wisdom yahoogroup quoting Aurobindo is r=
elevant to this thread. Aurobindo's commentaries on Veda and Upanishat are =
the best and most insightful that you can find today. He is undoubtedly a r=
ishi. His diagnosis of the situation is very appropriate even today and bea=
utiful to read. I am copying it below.
 
When I say we need spiritual sadha=
kas who achieve detachment and equanimity and become instruments of Mother =
and when Aurobindo says we need a "nucleus of men in whom Shakti is develop=
ed to its uttermost extent", we are essentially saying the same thing in di=
fferent words. I am confident that the day will come when Aurobindo's desir=
e is fulfilled, within the next few decades. Unfortunately, I sometimes see=
 people who have the potential to be in the "nucleus" that Aurobindo refers=
 to joining the frustrated crowds on the periphery.
 
Rahul asked anna to "=
empower" him and others. A vessel of mud has to be baked before one can pou=
r water in it. Even a rishi like Vivekananda needed to do intense sadhana t=
o purify himself for several years before he could be empowered by Ramakris=
hna.
 
If one really wants to strengthen sanatana dharma, one needs to accu=
mulate spiritual shakti (and not waste it). I suggest the following. Take a=
 homam (e.g. Chandi homam or Ganapathi homam or Rama homam etc) and do it e=
veryday with some niyamas. Or take a mantra or prayer (e.g. Chandipath or V=
ishnu sahasra naam or manahamantra etc) and do it everyday for 2-3 hours wi=
th some niyamas. I can suggest the following niyamas - close the eyes, keep=
 the back straight during meditation and minimize body movement. Do the rit=
ual at the same time everyday at the same place (as much as possible). Main=
tain physical brahmacharya atleast and eventually mental too. Strive to get=
 control over emotions and not become angry or jealous or lustful etc, as o=
ne's shakti leaks (gets wasted) whenever one loses self control.
 
Sadhakas=
 engaging in intense sadhana, purifying themselves and achieving utter equa=
nimity and detachment will accumulate so much spiritual and mental shakti t=
hat they will combine and shake the world in the coming decades and establi=
sh sanatana dharma for a few centuries to come. It is for this purpose that=
 Mother asked my guru Manish Pandit, when She appeared in front of him in M=
arch 2006 at the Kalikambal temple in Chennai, to teach a very simple homam=
 procedure to interested sadhakas across the world without differentiating =
on the basis of class, caste and creed. Homam will enable several people to=
 purify themselves and accumulate spiritual shakti.
 
OK, now read what Aur=
obindo says.
 
Best regards,
Narasimha
 
